Canny Maphanga Suspected counterfeit bank notes were found during a raid. (Supplied) Multimedia    ·   User Galleries   ·   News in Pictures
	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Three men have been arrested after being found in possession of suspected counterfeit bank notes during a raid in Gezina, Pretoria, police say. The raid took place on Wednesday after the police received a tip-off. "The suspects were found inside one of the units at a block of flats. The suspected counterfeit notes were recovered in a lock-up garage that is reportedly reserved to that unit," Tshwane police spokesperson Captain Daniel Mavimbela said in a statement. The suspects - aged 19, 38 and 39 - will be charged with possession of suspected counterfeit cash and are expected to appear in the Pretoria Magistrate's Court soon. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  